plot_rt: In 1970s Spain, a boy (Alberto Amarilla) who wants to be a poet falls for an aspiring ballerina (María Ruiz).
A woman (Anna Lise Phillips) awakens from a coma with no memory of her past. As she slowly learns disturbing truths about herself she realizes that she must wage a battle for her own redemption.
Satta and Seero's enduring love faces many obstacles. Their journey depicts the resilience of true passion as they strive to be together.
Laura accepts a role in a play as an act of rebellion against her mother. To help her show her emotions on stage, the play's director pushes her to bring out her vulnerability and anger.
Ralph, a cemetery worker, must take care of a young girl for three days without anyone finding out.
A look at what the world of international street performing busker is like. These people chose this path to make a living, despite the challenges they have to face.
The narrative unfolds, exposing a tale of betrayal, revenge and the collateral of unchecked desires.
The power of love and the mind bends a man's reality when he is stressed.
Journalist Im Sang-jin investigates reports of online public opinion manipulation, and is confronted with an unbelievable truth.

John "Breacher" Wharton (Arnold Schwarzenegger) leads an elite DEA task force. Its latest mission is a high-stakes raid on a safe house owned by one of the world's deadliest drug cartels. Wharton and his team (Sam Worthington, Terrence Howard, Joe Manganiello) complete the mission successfully but secretly steal $10 million for themselves. They think their work is done -- until, one-by-one, the commandos are mysteriously killed. As the body count rises, everyone becomes a suspect.
Michael and Jackie record their romance from meeting through marriage. As family tensions ignite, the camera sees a much different story.

Reuniting the director, writer and stars of Forrest Gump, Here is an original film about multiple families and a special place they inhabit. The story travels through generations, capturing the most relatable of human experiences. Zemeckis (Forrest Gump, Castaway, Who Framed Roger Rabbit, Contact, Back to the Future) directs from a screenplay by Eric Roth (Forrest Gump, Killers of the Flower Moon, Dune, A Star is Born) and him. Told much in the style of the acclaimed graphic novel by Richard McGuire on which it is based, Tom Hanks and Robin Wright star in a tale of love, loss, laughter and life, all of which happen right Here.
Two men avenge a woman's death.
A former member of the Ku Klux Klan learns tolerance through love and faith when he's taken in by an African American reverend.

Four women embark on different paths to healing after a devastating betrayal by a pivotal figure in each of their lives. June's success as a motivational speaker masks her inner turmoil. Their lives intersect as they try to overcome their demons.
An idealistic FBI agent (Daniel Radcliffe) goes under cover to infiltrate a white supremacist group that's plotting an act of terror.

title_imdb: Bill & Nancy: The Story Before Oliver Twist

plot_rt: Every summer, working-class families enjoy waterfront living in a scrappy trailer park off the coast of Virginia. When the relentless march of capitalism threatens their shabby Shangri-La, the denizens of Inlet View face the inevitable, and reveal the secrets to a rich life.
A woman and her family travel to Africa to meet a scientist who lives with wild animals.
A woman is stalked by a monstrous clown who seems to know her every move.
